<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5234> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5234" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Pressed against Gabinius the charge of extortion, on which he was convicted (Cic. QF 3.1.15, and 2.1, and 3.2; Rab. Post. 7 and 32; Val. Max. 8.1, abs. 3; see 55, Promagistrates). Probably the Memmius who prosecuted Domitius Calvinus for bribery (Cic. Att. 4.17.5, cf. 18.3; QF 3.2.3, and 3.2)." .
